{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/daveslutzkin/dev/ai-barometer","sessionId":"a02fdee5-269d-4998-9f4f-bcc01368783a","version":"2.1.37","gitBranch":"main","slug":"shiny-stargazing-dove","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Prebuilt Releases + Install Script\n\n## Context\nUsers currently need Rust installed to build ai-barometer from source. We want a `curl | sh` one-liner that downloads a prebuilt binary and sets everything up. macOS only (Apple Silicon + Intel).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n### 1. GitHub Actions release workflow (`.github/workflows/release.yml`)\n\nTriggered on tag push (`v*`). Builds two macOS binaries and creates a GitHub Release.\n\n**Build matrix:**\n| Target | Runner |\n|---|---|\n| `aarch64-apple-darwin` | `macos-latest` (arm64) |\n| `x86_64-apple-darwin` | `macos-13` (Intel) |\n\n**Steps per matrix entry:**\n1. Checkout code\n2. Install Rust stable\n3. `cargo build --release`\n4. Create tarball: `ai-barometer-{target}.tar.gz` containing the binary\n5. Upload as release artifact\n\n**Final job** (needs both builds):\n- Create GitHub Release from the tag\n- Attach both tarballs\n\n### 2. Install script (`install.sh` at repo root)\n\nA POSIX shell script users run via:\n```\ncurl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TeamCadenceAI/ai-barometer/main/install.sh | sh\n```\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Detect OS (must be macOS, else error)\n2. Detect architecture (`arm64` → `aarch64-apple-darwin`, `x86_64` → `x86_64-apple-darwin`)\n3. Fetch the latest release tag from GitHub API (`/repos/TeamCadenceAI/ai-barometer/releases/latest`)\n4. Download the correct tarball from the release assets\n5. Extract binary to `/usr/local/bin` (with `sudo` if needed)\n6. Run `ai-barometer install` to set up git hooks + initial hydration\n\n**Error handling:** Clear messages if not macOS, if download fails, if no release found.\n\n### 3. CI test workflow (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`)\n\nSince there's no CI yet, add a basic one that runs on every push/PR:\n- `cargo fmt -- --check`\n- `cargo clippy -- -D warnings`\n- `cargo test`\n\nThis protects the release workflow from shipping broken binaries.\n\n## Files to create/modify\n- **Create:** `.github/workflows/release.yml`\n- **Create:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml`\n- **Create:** `install.sh`\n\n## Verification\n1. Run `shellcheck install.sh` (if available) or manually review for POSIX correctness\n2. Run `cargo test` to make sure nothing is broken\n3. Dry-run: test install.sh locally with a mock release URL\n4. Tag and push `v0.1.0` to trigger the first release build\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/daveslutzkin/.claude/projects/-Users-daveslutzkin-dev-ai-barometer/4ddb4e17-6140-4140-8953-7aeb88024c1c.jsonl"},"uuid":"5e4a6c19-8b85-4baa-bb99-4127721e547e","timestamp":"2026-02-09T11:27:42.764Z","planContent":"# Plan: Prebuilt Releases + Install Script\n\n## Context\nUsers currently need Rust installed to build ai-barometer from source. We want a `curl | sh` one-liner that downloads a prebuilt binary and sets everything up. macOS only (Apple Silicon + Intel).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n### 1. GitHub Actions release workflow (`.github/workflows/release.yml`)\n\nTriggered on tag push (`v*`). Builds two macOS binaries and creates a GitHub Release.\n\n**Build matrix:**\n| Target | Runner |\n|---|---|\n| `aarch64-apple-darwin` | `macos-latest` (arm64) |\n| `x86_64-apple-darwin` | `macos-13` (Intel) |\n\n**Steps per matrix entry:**\n1. Checkout code\n2. Install Rust stable\n3. `cargo build --release`\n4. Create tarball: `ai-barometer-{target}.tar.gz` containing the binary\n5. Upload as release artifact\n\n**Final job** (needs both builds):\n- Create GitHub Release from the tag\n- Attach both tarballs\n\n### 2. Install script (`install.sh` at repo root)\n\nA POSIX shell script users run via:\n```\ncurl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TeamCadenceAI/ai-barometer/main/install.sh | sh\n```\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Detect OS (must be macOS, else error)\n2. Detect architecture (`arm64` → `aarch64-apple-darwin`, `x86_64` → `x86_64-apple-darwin`)\n3. Fetch the latest release tag from GitHub API (`/repos/TeamCadenceAI/ai-barometer/releases/latest`)\n4. Download the correct tarball from the release assets\n5. Extract binary to `/usr/local/bin` (with `sudo` if needed)\n6. Run `ai-barometer install` to set up git hooks + initial hydration\n\n**Error handling:** Clear messages if not macOS, if download fails, if no release found.\n\n### 3. CI test workflow (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`)\n\nSince there's no CI yet, add a basic one that runs on every push/PR:\n- `cargo fmt -- --check`\n- `cargo clippy -- -D warnings`\n- `cargo test`\n\nThis protects the release workflow from shipping broken binaries.\n\n## Files to create/modify\n- **Create:** `.github/workflows/release.yml`\n- **Create:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml`\n- **Create:** `install.sh`\n\n## Verification\n1. Run `shellcheck install.sh` (if available) or manually review for POSIX correctness\n2. Run `cargo test` to make sure nothing is broken\n3. Dry-run: test install.sh locally with a mock release URL\n4. Tag and push `v0.1.0` to trigger the first release build\n"}
